(260, 8, 'essay', 'During the design stage of a system development project, certain activities are undertaken. Name three activities typically performed during this stage.', 3, '1. Designing the user interface. 2. Creating data flow diagrams. 3. Developing system architecture.', 'Creating a user-friendly interface is a key part of the design process.Data flow diagrams help visualize the flow of information within the system.System architecture outlines the technical structure and components of the system.', NULL, NULL, NULL),
(261, 8, 'essay', 'Why should a system being developed be subjected to more than one test? Provide two reasons.', 2, '1. To identify and fix different types of errors that may arise in various conditions. 2. To verify that the system meets all user requirements.', 'Multiple tests ensure the system performs well under different circumstances. Testing ensures that the system functions as expected from the user\'s perspective.', NULL, NULL, NULL),
(262, 8, 'essay', 'When writing a program, the system is often broken into modules. What are two advantages of this modular approach?', 2, '1. It simplifies debugging by isolating errors within specific modules. 2. It allows for parallel development, speeding up the project timeline.', 'Modular design makes it easier to identify and fix problems. Different teams can work on individual modules simultaneously, increasing efficiency.', NULL, NULL, NULL),
(263, 8, 'essay', 'The new system for Kazizela Manufactures will require additional hardware to computerize their manual order processing system, apart from the computer itself. Name two additional hardware components and give a reason for each one of them.', 4, '1. Printer. To print invoices or shipping labels. 2. Barcode scanner. To efficiently scan product codes for tracking and orders.', 'A printer is necessary for producing hard copies of orders or reports.The printer would facilitate documentation and shipping processes. A barcode scanner would speed up inventory management. A barcode scanner helps in streamlining the order and inventory processes.', NULL, NULL, NULL),
(264, 8, 'essay', 'Kazizela Manufactures decides to advertise on the internet after computerizing their system. What are two advantages and two disadvantages of internet advertising?', 4, ' Advantage 1: Reaches a wider audience quickly. Advantage 2: Cost-effective compared to traditional advertising. Disadvantage 1: May lead to privacy concerns if user data is mishandled. Disadvantage 2: Increased competition, making it harder to stand out.', 'Internet advertising has a global reach and can attract customers from around the world. Online advertising is generally cheaper than print, radio, or TV ads. Online ads often rely on tracking user behavior, which can cause privacy issues. Online spaces are crowded, so companies must invest heavily to differentiate their ads.', NULL, NULL, NULL),
(265, 8, 'essay', 'In evaluating the system developed for Kazizela Manufactures or any other system development, three key items should be considered. What are they?', 3, ' 1. User satisfaction. 2. System efficiency. 3. Data accuracy and integrity', 'Ensuring that the system meets the needs and expectations of the users is vital. Evaluating whether the system meets performance standards in terms of speed and resource usage is important. Ensuring that the system processes and stores data correctly and securely is essential for reliability.', NULL, NULL, NULL),
